However, there will be no real party atmosphere - not only because of the official speech of the minister but also because the celebration was scheduled for the afternoon.
The Ministry of Agriculture invites on 20. January to a New Year's Reception, the Christmas party of the Ministry is cancelled this time.
One hundred guests are invited to the Vajdahunyad Chateau in the city park ("Városliget"); according to the department, the expenses amount to 1,000 forints per guest.
As reported by the press department, it will be a very simple standing reception to which only foreign diplomats accredited in Hungary will be invited.
The receptions, which are held every year, traditionally begin with a short speech by the minister and end with a restrained feast.
As the corresponding press offices report on [origo] request, there will be neither a Christmas party at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs nor at the Ministry of Education.
When asked about the cost of the Christmas party, the press department of the Ministry of the Environment could not provide any information.
