Holidays are not everywhere Holidays
In Hungary, public holidays are regulated by law, so the practice of rescheduling the working days around the public holidays has become established, but the coming year will bring us fewer such days.
Also in the EU and in America something else is understood by "holiday".
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between state holidays and non-working days.
Non-working days are usually religious holidays, or are associated with significant historical events.
For example, we also celebrate New Year: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year are non-working days - the latter alone so that those celebrating New Year's Eve can rest.
Throughout the year we have a total of fourteen holidays.
The public holidays are 15 March, which commemorates the revolution of 1848, and 23 October, which commemorates the revolution of 1956.
On 20 August the foundation of the state is celebrated, on 1 May the work, on 1 and 2 November we commemorate our dead.
In addition, there are two holidays each at Easter, Pentecost, and Christmas.
Since our state, national, or religious holidays seldom fall on a weekend, the practice of "working-day shift" has proven effective in cases where we would work only one day before or after the holiday.
The price of the extended weekends, however, is that we work on the Saturdays before very well, or have to go to school.
For many years, the Labour Minister has laid down in a separate regulation when this day, which falls before or after the holiday, should ultimately be worked out.
The legislation applies to all employers and employees, public employees and civil servants alike.
Only companies and establishments, in which the enterprise is continued without interruption, thus also on the holidays, are excluded.
This year, the work regulations are only somewhat confused by the holidays at the end of the year: From the 24th of December, life in this country formally stops, as most take time compensation for the days between Christmas and New Year's Eve, or the specially abolished holiday.
Next year, more public holidays will fall in the middle of the week, i.e. at the end of the week, so that there will be less rescheduling of working days than this year.
The calendar is first "turned upside down" around the day of work, so that people can stay at home for four days at a time.
Saturday, April 26th will be a working day, so Friday, May 2nd can be a rest day.
The second rescheduling is related to the holiday on 23 October: on Saturday, 18 October, the Friday, 24 October will have to be processed in advance.
The end of the year, however, will be completely dedicated to the holidays, after everything will be on hold from 24 December, even if New Year ’ s Eve falls on a Wednesday.
Six deterrent trifles to annoy colleagues
T he mails that we forget to send out, voicemail messages that we never receive - harmless lies that we no longer notice: They bring "color" into everyday life at work.
The question is simply whether to get used to these minor inconveniences, or rather to face the challenge and consciously try to avoid these ambiguous, for other annoying situations.
Tips.
"Sorry, I forgot to tell you that someone from the marketing department called" - says a colleague.
That you missed a meeting?
At best, you regret it and try to make up for it by perhaps calling the marketing department and remorsefully confessing that you forgot to align the message (this is the less common method).
Usually the matter is dismissed with an apology.
Before getting tangled up in embarrassing excuses, one should consider how to prepare truly unpleasant moments for one ’ s colleagues and try to avoid these situations consciously.
Borrowed something that does not belong to yourself?
There is nothing more annoying than reaching for a document, office supplies, or phone, but it is not there.
Yesterday the stapler was still on the desk - this morning it is gone?
Or is the lost ballpoint pen discovered on the desk of a colleague?
You should not borrow anything from colleagues without asking, because they are rightly annoyed when they find that something has got away.
So, no envelopes or post it from the office in your pocket, because it could even meet you: none more there, if you need it urgently.
Getting chatted about the private life of colleagues?
There is no effective way to stop gossip that has already begun.
Who with whom, what made?
Where and why?
If possible, one should not bind the information (or conjectures) about the private life of the colleagues to the nose of everyone!
And if someone opens up and reveals his innermost secret, we should not abuse this trust!
It is best to remain silent like a grave, rather than to pass the message on to those who are not present, even if others also know about the problems of the colleague.
Reported ill for no reason?
When you call the office to report illness, citing agonizing headaches, because you are feeling uncomfortable at the moment, or simply want to rest, you should be clear about one thing: your own work, unpostponable errands, projects with fixed dates must now be done by your colleagues instead of yourself.
So do not play along badly with your colleagues!
If you already know the day before that you won ’ t be able to get into the office the next day, or that something might happen, which is why you have to stay at home, you should report it in time so that neither the colleagues nor the boss are unexpectedly confronted with the absence.
Crying, giggling, phoning
One is just absorbed in his work, but is suddenly disturbed by the loud giggling of his female colleagues?
Inadvertently listened to a telephone conversation, which one should not have heard better?
You should not annoy your colleagues with buzzing, singing, loud conversations (which you carry over their heads), trampling, constant scolding or grumbling.
All of this can be very disturbing, even if they are not particularly engrossed in a task (writing, planning, organizing).
Are the others always to blame?
If a project is not completed on time, if you have forgotten to send an important letter or important messages, you should not blame others for your own forgetfulness!
As far as possible, one should not stop at the chaos in the office or the noisy colleagues!
It is best to admit your mistakes and apologize if others were also affected!
The question of how to make up for the mistake or make up for the omission is all too appropriate.
In the office - a feeling like home?
Practice pants and slippers: Comfortable for the home, but has nothing to lose in the office!
Not even if the workplace would allow it, you should dress so casually!
Just don't get too sloppy - you should respect your colleagues as well as yourself so much that you dress accordingly in the office - if desired, also pretty and elegant!
Want to make it all right - or how to become uninteresting to others
Stop and go the traffic, the car in the middle of the morning traffic jam.
A strange melody sounds from the radio: the sound of a violin, paired with electronic effects.
I turn the volume higher.
The tempo changes, to the previous sounds comes the bass, and as a real sound jewel a female choir.
It is the song "Wings of Love" by Zagar, which is played on mr2.
The local music scene did not spoil us with qualitative Electropop for a long time.
But now you even see the traffic jam differently when you listen to Zagar ’ s new album.
The release of Yonderboi, many new and exciting productions from the local digital underground scene are slowly contributing to a change in the overall picture, and even if the garage rock with its guitar geckish is "in" again, the local electropop proves: There is something new under the sun.
Balázs Zságer started in Pécs, played in the band Yonderboi himself, before he started his own way - maybe because an inn can't take two pipers.
The breakthrough with his project (Zagar) and his music, which blends elements from jazz, electronic, and pop, he only managed to achieve when they approached him with the request to compose the soundtrack for a film (e.g.
"Szezon" by Ferenc Török).
The band, which had initially performed in smaller clubs, only became known to the general public when the magazine "wan2" listed their first album from 2002 among the top 50 domestic albums and named Zagar, together with Yonderboi, almost the only marketable trendsetter in the West.
Without a doubt, Zagar and his band were "trendy", but nobody was interested in whether they also liked to wear this brand.
The band reacted as it should: with a new, even better album.
The new album "Cannot Walk Fly Instead" could open up new paths for them, but even the title expresses the desire for continuity with the Pécs years.
The expression comes from the time when Balázs Zságer was on tour with another band.
The airy, flying allusion would be fine, but apart from the ethereal character of the music, the loud guitar - corresponding to the zeitgeist and the trends - the influences of rock 'n' roll are noticeable.
With these songs the singer György Ligeti, who lives in England and works with the band "The Puzzle", introduced himself at the premiere in the Millenáris.
One song from the album even made it to a radio hit - mr2 Petőfi, which broadcasts pop music from early to late, successively set the catchy tune for the listeners with the track "Wings of Love", which was recorded with the participation of six local female singers ("Underground Divas").
All right then (?).
hvg.hu asked Balázs Zságer.
hvg.hu: This new hit raises the question: To what extent is your music reserved for a certain class?
Balázs Zságer: The term "Schichtmusik" doesn't mean much to me.
In my opinion there are two castes in pop music, not mainstream and underground, or alternative and pop, but commercial and honest.
Even the so-called alternative or underground music can be shallow and meaningless, just as it can only be produced for sale, which makes it commercial music.
Even a good pop number can arise from an honest motif.
The receptiveness of the listener also functions according to this principle, independent of languages and national borders.
hvg.hu: Do you see a difference in the openness of Hungarian and foreign audiences towards your music?
B. Zs.: In foreign countries, especially west of us, pop music has a greater tradition.
Not only teenagers or twens go to concerts, but also the older audience.
They follow the trends in pop music that are happening around them much more attentively, because they also consider them to be a part of contemporary culture.
hvg.hu: What is the role of the audience in your work?
Is it important who, where, how many listen to your music?
B. Zs.: Of course it ’ s a good feeling to see that more and more people come to our concerts.
But we never composed for the market.
With us, music is not created to serve a purpose, but for a specific reason.
The role of the audience can usually be felt at concerts, where there is already a mutual interaction, but this is only possible in the intangible changes of the moment.
Nevertheless, I noticed one thing: if you want to please everyone, you are no longer interesting.
hvg.hu: How far do you want to follow the example of Yonderboi?
He is on the road as a soloist and has built up his career more in the West.
B. Zs: We don ’ t really go his way, not to mention trying to interpret this into our music again and again.
We see ourselves more as team players who trust the musical presence of the other and let it unfold.
In the beginning, of course, comparisons of our work with that of Yonderboi were inevitable, since several of us come from his band and have taken a different path.
hvg.hu: In the charts of mr2 Petőfi, "Wings of Love" comes first.
Many have only heard the name Zagar in connection with this number.
Was the opening deliberately staged with a slightly more popular style towards a wider audience?
B. Zs: We had no plans to write a hit, which would then serve as a driving force for the album.
This song is about more.
It was meant to be the finale of the album, with which we wanted to dissolve the orgy of sound and the somewhat more difficult themes.
hvg.hu: How did you choose the six female singers?
Why just them, what was the guiding principle?
B. Z.: The basic idea was to make a gospel-like choir.
Then the idea came to put the choir together from talented soloists from the local music scene.
This is how the choir of six came into being - i.e. Sena, Edina Kutzora, Judie Jay, Bori Péterfy, Enikő Hodosi [Neo], Juci Németh - which we named "Underground Divas".
hvg.hu: Did you want to have the song the same way, or did the girls help shape it?
B. Zs: The number has been available in the instrumental version for a long time, but when the material for the album was ready, we thought that this number still "needs" something.
The chord sequence formally demanded a vocal part.
I sang the melody the same night, later they learned the girls.
It all came almost immediately and frighteningly spontaneous.
I can remember, I was quite electrified at that time, but it also needed the "Divas".
With my voice alone the song would never have become so powerful.
hvg.hu: But on the record as well as at the concert you had the impression that the girls were in the background.
There is no solo part (apart from Judy Jay ’ s short solo), they have no role of their own, sing together completely and are no louder than the music, so their singing is not only accompanied by the music.
They were also on stage in the back.
Is it deliberate?
B.Zs.: The fact that they stood behind was due to purely technical problems.
However, we deliberately wanted to give them no solo roles.
The number is also about forgetting one ’ s ego a little, forgetting who has come from where and where, let ’ s just let those particular wings, the wings of love, lift us up.
I would like others to feel the euphoric state that we felt when the song was written.
hvg.hu: What was the most elaborate song?
B. Zs: In the musical work actually none, there were rather more difficult tasks in mixing.
For example "Dorian Gray's Dilemma", where I play on a concert piano, or "Rock'n'Roll Goes To The Girls", where the groove didn't want to work any longer, but little by little everything has come together, like a puzzle.
hvg.hu: What is your favourite song from the new album?
B. Zs.: That changes constantly with the concerts and also now that I have released the album.
Currently they are "Prophet Is A Fool", "Escape From The Earth" and the track "Never The Same".
