Which insurance is best suited for me?
Motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves high costs, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an policyholder.
This agreement is stipulated in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the company shall receive the agreed insurance premium and in return shall be obliged to submit the corresponding amount of compensation in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance, which is made up of several factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of the statistics, so that higher premiums are also due if the risk of accidents is higher.
As a result, both 25 + year-olds and women will have to contribute less, as statistics show that their prudence means that these groups have a lower accident rate.
The same is true of married people, who, according to statistical data and therefore also to the conviction of companies, are less prone to accidents than single people.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle impair the frequency of driving and thus the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
Insurance companies must take a whole series of points into account when setting the premium.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
At this point we list the most important points to consider when selecting an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance- but also a price-oriented choice.
There are numerous obstacles to choosing low-cost insurance for people under 25 years of age, such as low driving experience and a young driving licence.
Even if it would be best to take out comprehensive insurance for an ideal insurance cover, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Careful drivers can choose a comprehensive insurance with excess, so that the services of a comprehensive insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount of the damage himself.
The amount will be determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the smaller the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain ’ s main representative at First Europa, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external damage caused by accidents, but not against damage to his own car.
Moreover, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here is a piece of advice.
If you are under 25 years old, it is up to you to reduce your insurance costs, so your credit will increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty involves an increase in the tariff in question.
The amount of credits and fines depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving experience.
Therefore, it makes most sense to opt for fully comprehensive insurance with excess.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the beginner's anxiety has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable to take out comprehensive insurance for a married customer who does not have children, of course only if the financial situation of the person in question allows it.
On the part of insurers, married couples with children are considered to have the lowest accident rate and their contributions are accordingly low.
In this case, a fully comprehensive insurance with excess (for an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit note, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which does not start until the third year of the vehicle.
They are generally more relaxed and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to set a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with excess (for an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, it must be said that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it entails high costs, which require a thorough choice to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
