The Scottish State Health Service must improve controls on criminal records of workers from outside Europe, said a member of the supervisory board. outside
The recommendation of the chief financial controller Robert Black came after a foreign doctor in Scotland was brought in connection with the attack on Glasgow airport in June.
Black also expressed concern that the Scottish National Health Service had no precise idea of the number of its foreign employees.
But his report pointed out that other important controls were carried out correctly in a sample of five health authorities.
The chief financial controller investigated personnel recruited outside the European Economic Area countries following the attack on Glasgow airport.
