The investigation also found that established control procedures had been largely respected by NHS authorities in Ayrshire, Arran, Grampian, Greater Glasgow and Clyde, Lanarkshire, and Lothian.
This includes passport, work permit, and qualification checks.
the Scottish Government is currently reviewing its policy and guidelines on pre-employment controls for foreign staff in the NHS.
